# Strict TypeScript and Lint Rules

- Enforce strict TypeScript for all changes.
- Do not use `any`; prefer exact types or `unknown` with narrowing.
- Do not ignore type errors or add type-bypass workarounds.
- Do not use `eslint-disable` comments, including single-line and file-level variants.
- Fix lint and type issues properly instead of suppressing checks.
